@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<hr />

<p>
    The Home Inventory System collects and stores only the data that you
    voluntarily provide when registering and cataloguing items. The following
    describes how your data is handled:
</p>

<h4>Account Data</h4>
<p>
    Your username is stored in plain text. Your password is <strong>never</strong>
    stored in plain text — it is hashed using SHA-256 before being saved to the
    database. Only you can authenticate with your credentials.
</p>

<h4>Inventory Data</h4>
<p>
    All inventory items you create are linked to your account and are not
    accessible to any other registered user. No inventory data is shared with
    third parties.
</p>

<h4>Cookies</h4>
<p>
    This application uses a single session cookie (<code>HomeInventoryAuthCookie</code>)
    to maintain your authenticated session. The cookie expires after 30 minutes
    of inactivity and is removed when you log out.
</p>

<a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-secondary mt-3">
    Back to Home
</a>
